Ross, J. M., Karney, B. R., Nguyen, T. P., & Bradbury, T. N. (2019).

Communication that is maladaptive for middle-class couples is adaptive for socioeconomically disadvantaged couples. Journal of Personality and Social Psychology, 116(4), 582597. https://doi.org/10.1037/pspi0000158

Last update at: 2023-05-22

Abstract / Key Points

Behavioral coding

APIM; longitudinal cross-level APIM

For couples of high risk of sociecnomic resources, husbands withdraw could deescalte the conflict, whereas for couples of low risk, withdrawal might instead signal selfishness
